<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVE TRAIN - Component Reassembly - Valve
        Covers
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Valve Covers</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use air powered tools when installing valve covers.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Right Side Valve Cover</emph>
        </para>
        <figure id="f2350496" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 213. Valve cover mounting hardware</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover stud bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new gasket if necessary. Then place valve cover onto rocker arm carrier. Install
                valve cover mounting bolts. Place stud bolts in correct locations to accommodate the glow plug relay
                bracket and other harness routing hardware. Leave finger tight until all bolts are started.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Continue to secure valve cover with remaining eight bolts. Tighten all mounting bolts to the
                special torque .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After the right side valve cover has been installed, the following parts can be installed.
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Glow plug relay bracket. See "Engine Electrical Section" for installation procedure.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Tube assembly, filter to right hand cylinder head.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Left Side Valve Cover</emph>
        </para>
        <figure id="f2350497" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 214. Valve cover mounting hardware</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover stud</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new gasket if necessary. Then place valve cover onto rocker arm carrier. Install
                valve cover mounting bolts. Place studs in correct locations to accommodate the ECM/IDM bracket and
                other harness routing hardware. Leave finger tight until all bolts are started. Tighten all bolts to the
                special torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filler extension tube onto valve cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed for any reason, install lifting eyes on the rear of each rocker arm carrier and
                one on the left front carrier. Tighten bolts to the special torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>After the left side valve cover has been installed, the following parts can be installed.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>ECM/IDM and bracket</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Breather hose assembly with pitot tube. See VGT Turbocharger.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Turbocharger air inlet duct. See VGT Turbocharger.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Tube assembly, filter to left hand cylinder head.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
